  "title": "IBM Planning Analytics (PA) Support Engineer (Ref 26330)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Perform impact analysis and resolve production defects.<br />• Manage daily operation chores/nightly data refresh in the IBM PA project and share observations if any.<br />• Fix data load failure, errors and warnings.<br />• Variance analysis/ data validation on monthly or quarterly close.<br />• Ensure data archival, restore and backup procedure.<br />• Upgrade and apply patches for IBM PA application (on premise IBM PA on GCC Cloud).<br />• Involve in cutover activities and well verse in executing the steps.<br />• Involve in deployment activities post fixes and enhancement.<br />• Work closely with infrastructure team for any environment issues, security, and concerns.<br /><br />Requirements<br />• Degree in Computer Science or relevant studies<br />• Minimum 4 years of relevant experience.<br />• Good understanding of the budgeting & forecasting process.<br />• Quick learner and able to understand implemented system functionality.<br />• Fundamental concepts:<br />• Cube, Dimension, element and hierarchy.<br />• Rules and feeders<br />• TI Process<br />• Data Type (numeric, string, consolidation)<br />• PAW, PAX, Pafe, TM1 web</p><p>Technical Skills: <br />a) Fundamental concepts:<br />• Cube, Dimension, element and hierarchy.<br />• Rules and feeders<br />• TI Process<br />• Data Type (numeric, string, consolidation)<br />• PAW, PAX, Pafe, TM1 web</p><p>b) PAW:<br />• Creating and managing cubes, dimensions, hierarchies, and subsets directly from PAW<br />• Defining relationships, attributes, and aliases<br />• Writing and testing rules within PAW’s rule editor<br />• Building and executing TI (TurboIntegrator) processes<br /></p><p>c) UI/UX:<br />• Designing intuitive PAW books and sheets<br />• Using widgets, tabs, selectors, and quick reports<br />• Best practices for layout, formatting, and usability</p><p>d) Security:<br />• Object security (cube, dimension, element, process, chore)<br />• Cell-level security rules and application security</p><p>e) Admin:<br />• Backup and recovery of PAW books and assets<br />• Deployment and upgrade</p><p>f) Others:<br />• Python Scripting<br />• Advance TI & Rule debugging<br />• Conditional Rule<br />• Feeder optimization<br />• Debugging feeders</p><p><br />Licence no :12C6060</p>",
